<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="371" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d371">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.57241/223</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Norwegian Minister (<persName type="from">Bachke</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <p>The Minister of Norway presents his compliments to the Secretary of
                                State and has the honor to inquire, with reference to the notes of
                                January 20, 1932, concerning free importation privileges for
                                Norwegian respectively American consular officials, [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] if the arrangement established through
                                the said notes is considered applicable to Norwegian consuls
                                residing in colonies and possessions of the United States of
                                America.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <dateline rendition="#left">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-25">February 25, 1932</date>.</dateline>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>